NUMBER 441
NAME Temple of Yarin, Deep Vault
CALL 33
ASTRAL
CHANNEL 441
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are in a deep cavern which was definately formed from powers other than
natural.  An etching upon the floor completely circles you, as if it were a
ward of some kind.  Long scratches lead from a forboding hole in the western
wall across the circular etching, breaking its former consistancy.  The hole
itself is covered by some kind of transparent material.  A silver plaque has
been affixed next to the door.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 70 ADJ1=87
ITEM 1 420 ADJ1=148
ITEM 2 400 ADJ1=292
EXIT SW 448
EXIT S 458
EXIT SE 447

IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER Even if you could get past the glass you have absolutely no intention of entering that place, it seems to sap your strength even at this distance.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You find it impossible to make out anything within the hole other than occasional wisps of vapor.
ENDIF

IFSAY Atnum_Trumin
  ECHO PLAYER The words seem to roll off your tongue of their own choice.  A thrumming power binds...and you feel yourself traveling.
  ECHO OTHERS As %N speaks the words you feel a binding force holding you...and suddenly %N is gone.
  MOVE 344
  AFFECT 344
  ECHO OTHERS %N suddenly appears in your midst.
  AFFECT 441
ENDIF

IFSAY Dulante_Safi_Lincage
  IFCARRY 1843 -1 
    IFVAR MUGTRACE = 1
      IFVAR MUGINTLINK1 ! 1
        ECHO ALL As the final words echo from %N's mouth, the traced outline of sigils begins to glow with a ruddy light.
        NEWITEM 9 744 ADJ1=145 VAL2=442
        REMOVEITEM 1  
        EQUAL MUGINTLINK1 1
      ELSE
        ECHO PLAYER The words of linking have been spoken, there is no point in repeating the procedure.
      ENDIF
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER Perhaps you should wait until you can work the magic upon the proper symbols.
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER Your words hold no power in this place.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY Tur_Unlin
  IFCARRY 1843 -1
    IFVAR MUGTRACE = 1
      IFVAR MUGINTLINK1 = 1
        ECHO ALL No sooner does %N finish speaking the words of closing than the granite wall shimmers and returns to normal.
        REMOVEITEM 9
        NEWITEM 1 420 ADJ1=148
        EQUAL MUGTRACE 0
        EQUAL MUGINTLINK1 0
      ELSE
        ECHO PLAYER Why close a portal which has not yet been opened?
      ENDIF
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER The words of power have nothing to effect.
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER Your words hold no power in this place.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TAP 1
  IFCARRY 1843 -1 
    IFVAR MUGTRACE ! 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO ALL %N traces a series of faint sigils on one of the cavern's walls.
      EQUAL MUGTRACE 1
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER Oh? And exactly what would you like to tap it for?
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 2
  CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER It has writing on it.
  ENDIF

IFPREVERB READ 2
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER It reads:%c%c"To All Things, There is a Beginning..."%c
ENDIF
