NUMBER 453
NAME Temple of Yarin, Loremistress's Office
*DESCRIPTION_START
A fireplace illuminates the room with a soft light. Shelves line the walls
with neatly stacked ancient scrolls and manuscripts recently dusted and
colour coded ribboned with the finest satin. An ancient white aelfen oak
trunk makes for a desk in the center of the room. Various vases that are
filled with healing herbs and a single scroll lays upon the desk next to a
crystal bowl filled with rose petals and a pale blue candle. Her chair is
cushioned with a feather pillow and made from a single log of the palest
uquart. A large comfortable sofa covered in the lightest silvery blue
doeskin faces the fireplace with two manuscripts that need to be catalogued
on it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
