NUMBER 445
NAME Library, Main Hall
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
ASTRAL
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This large room is filled with bookshelves. Although many are still empty
they are being filled as the library imports books and has new ones 
scribed. The ceiling glows with stars, planets and moons. It is a map
of the solar system as seen from the view of the Great Moon.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1028
ITEM 1 423
EXTEND 1 entitled,"Astronomy"
ITEM 2 60 VAL2=443 

IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER On the bookcase a book entitled "Astronomy" catchs your eye.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB OPEN 1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR sean = 1
    ECHO PLAYER The book is already open.
  ENDIF
    IFVAR sean = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You carefully open the book to the first page.
      ECHO OTHERS %N carefully opens the book to the first page.
      EQUAL sean 1
      EQUAL sean1 1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF

IFPREVERB CLOSE 1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR sean = 0
    ECHO PLAYER The book is already closed.
  ENDIF
    IFVAR sean = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You carefully close the book.
      ECHO OTHERS %N carefully closes the book.
      EQUAL sean 0
      EQUAL sean1 0
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
 
IFPREVERB READ 1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR sean1 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER                        Andorian Astronomy
    ECHO PLAYER     
    ECHO PLAYER     There are three hundred forty three days in the Andorian year.
    ECHO PLAYER   The year is divided into twelve months, roughly twenty eight days
    ECHO PLAYER   each. The months, in order, are Abra,Brama,Manta,Dretmar,Alabea,
    ECHO PLAYER   Phobrus,Melma,Banamae,Olum,Mixus,Farnum and Folster.    
    ECHO PLAYER      
    ECHO PLAYER     There are three moons that revolve around Andor. The largest 
    ECHO PLAYER   is the golden-hued Great Moon which appears about the size of a
    ECHO PLAYER   saucer. The next largest moon is called Phulcus, a dull-grey disk
    ECHO PLAYER   about half the size of the Great Moon. The smallest is called Shakar,
    ECHO PLAYER   the Crimson Moon, which appears as a small red dot.
    ECHO PLAYER    
    ECHO PLAYER                                              Equinox, Lord Astromancer
    ECHO OTHERS %N reads the book.
  ENDIF  
ENDIF
;      
